Brand-New Lifestyle of Light, Luxury and Family Flexibility

*** This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time ***
In a prime position enjoying every Keilor East advantage, this just-completed 4BR residence delivers an exceptional family environment with its architectural excellence, floorplan versatility and first-class features throughout. Quality at every turn, the home's impressive interior boasts alternate master bedrooms on each level (both with WIRs and private ensuites) together with two additional bedrooms, stylish main bathroom and guest powder room (fourth WC). Adding to its appeal is a large study area/retreat (upstairs) and expansive open-plan living/dining area enhanced by a gourmet stone-bench kitchen with mirrored splashbacks, premium Smeg appliances and adjoining butler's pantry. Other luxuries include zoned ducted heating and refrigerated cooling, alarm system and video intercom, high ceilings and efficient LED lighting, along with a family-sized laundry and large under-stair storeroom, quality flooring and soft-close cabinetry throughout. Completing the picture is a back garden with lawn area and decking, plus an internally-accessed garage (remote-control) and additional driveway parking space. Walking distance to primary and secondary schools (including PEGS), Dinah Parade shops and eateries, it's also close to new Keilor East Leisure Centre (under construction), local parks and Steele Creek trails, public transport and easy freeway access.

Description:
Ideal Entry, Investment or Downsize Opportunity!
Please register your interest in this property so that we can ensure you are included in the Virtual Auction and/or contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior to the Virtual Auction 14th July at 5pm.
*** This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time ***
In the heart of Keilor East with the area's many attractions all close by, this freestanding rear villa is sure to make an impression with its generous single-level floorplan, quality inclusions and private surrounds. Impeccably presented from start to finish, the home's light and bright interior comprises three spacious bedrooms (two with built-in robes and ceiling fans), together with a spotless central bathroom and powder room (second WC). Adding to its appeal is a wonderfully versatile open-plan living/dining area accompanied by a well-appointed kitchen complete with soft-close drawers, ample cupboard space, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Along with ducted heating and split-system air conditioning for year-round comfort, the home also includes a full-size laundry, video intercom and NBN connection. Step outside enjoy the private rear courtyard with expansive undercover entertaining area, plus a secure storeroom, remote-control garage. Adjacent to Shelley Street Reserve, it's also walking distance to Centreway's popular shops and eateries, local parks, schools (including PEGS) and Keilor East Leisure Centre, as well as public transport and easy access to the Calder Freeway.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance.
Thank you.

Description:
Ultimate Family Lifestyle Package
In response to COVID-19 this auction will be held online. Please contact us to obtain your registration link.
Inspections are by private appointment only.
Beautifully presented and ready for your family to move in, this solid brick four bedroom, two bathroom home offers relaxed living on an impressive allotment of approximately 835m2. Arched walkways open to multiple living spaces, including a spaciously sundrenched front lounge, versatile yet private dining room and fully equipped kitchen/meals fitted with stainless steel appliances, walk-in pantry, breakfast bar and filament lighting. Crafted for entertaining, the remarkable all-weather alfresco, fitted with electric blinds, features a suitable wood fire heater, while flowing into the landscaped backyard comprising garden shed, lockup double garage and gated undercover carport for multiple vehicles. The master bedroom boasts a convenient walk-through-robe to ensuite, as the central bathroom and separate toilet are flanked by the other bedrooms; two with built-in-robes. Further extras include polished hardwood floors, ducted heating, roomy laundry with backyard access, hallway storage, extensive driveway providing ample off-street-parking and pristine gardens. With something for everyone, it's moments from multiple schools, Keilor Central, community centres, parkland, Keilor Plains station and freeways.
